<div class="page">
  <article class="column">
    <h4 class="title">Lorem Ipsum</h4>
    <p>This column is capped at 680px. Resize the window to see it fill the available space until hitting the cap, then center.</p>
    <p>With plain CSS, <code>margin-inline: auto</code> is all you really need here.</p>
  </article>
</div>

<style>
  .page {
    padding: 16px;
    border: 1px dashed #afb8c1;
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: #f6f8fa;
  }
  .column {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    background: white;
    padding: 18px 22px;
    border: 1px solid #d0d7de;
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: #1f2328;
  }
  .title {
    margin: 0 0 0.5em;
    font-family: var(--mono);
  }
  .column p { margin: 0 0 0.7em; }
  .column p:last-child { margin: 0; }
  .column code { background: #eaeef2; padding: 1px 4px; border-radius: 3px; }
</style>
